\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.html#PowerSeries.weierstrassDiv\">/ʷ</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.html#PowerSeries.weierstrassMod\">%ʷ</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `q` and `r` are quotient and remainder in the Weierstrass division `f / g`, then they are\nequal to `f /ʷ g` and `f %ʷ g`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.html#PowerSeries.IsWeierstrassDivision.unique","kind":"theorem","line":610,"name":"PowerSeries.IsWeierstrassDivision.unique","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.lean#L610-L615"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.html#PowerSeries.IsWeierstrassDivision.eq_zero\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsWeierstrassDivision</span>.<span class=\"name\">eq_zero</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/LocalRing/Defs.html#IsLocalRing\">IsLocalRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_a