 class=\"fn\">q</span> <span class=\"fn\">r</span> <span class=\"fn\">I</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.html#PowerSeries.IsWeierstrassDivisionAt.mk","kind":"ctor","line":116,"name":"PowerSeries.IsWeierstrassDivisionAt.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.lean#L116-L116"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.html#PowerSeries.isWeierstrassDivisionAt_iff\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">isWeierstrassDivisionAt_iff</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f </span><span class=\"fn\">g </span><span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries\">PowerSeries</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial\">Polynomial</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">I</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Defs.html#Ideal\">Ideal</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.html#PowerSeries.IsWeierstrassDivisionAt\">IsWeierstrassDivisionAt</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">q</span> <span class=\"fn\">r</span> <span class=\"fn\">I</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">r</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Degree/Defs.html#Polynomial.degree\">degree</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.map\">map</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Quotient/Defs.html#Ideal.Quotient.mk\">Ideal.Quotient.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span>)</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Order.html#PowerSeries.order\">order</a></span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENat/Basic.html#ENat.toNat\">toNat</a></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">q</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">r</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.html#PowerSeries.isWeierstrassDivisionAt_iff","kind":"theorem","line":115,"name":"PowerSeries.isWeierstrassDivisionAt_iff","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.lean#L115-L115"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.html#PowerSeries.IsWeierstrassDivisionAt\"><span class=\"name\">PowerSeries</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsWeierstrassDivisionAt</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f </span><span class=\"fn\">g </span><span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries\">PowerSeries</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial\">Polynomial</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">I</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Defs.html#Ideal\">Ideal</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `f`, `g` be power series over `A`, `I` be an ideal of `A`,\n`PowerSeries.IsWeierstrassDivisionAt f g q r I` is a `Prop` which asserts that a power series\n`q` and a polynomial `r` of degree `< n` satisfy `f = g * q + r`, where `n` is the order of the\nimage of `g` in `(A / I)⟦X⟧` (defined to be zero if such image is zero, in which case\nit's mathematically not considered). ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.html#PowerSeries.IsWeierstrassDivisionAt","kind":"structure","line":110,"name":"PowerSeries.IsWeierstrassDivisionAt","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WeierstrassPreparation.lean#L110-L118"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.RingTheory.LocalRing.ResidueField.Basic","Mathlib.RingTheory.Polynomial.Eisenstein.Distinguished","Mathlib.RingTheory.PowerSeries.CoeffMulMem","Mathlib.RingTheory.PowerSeries.Inverse","Mathlib.RingTheory.PowerSeries.Trunc"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.RingTheory.PowerSeries.WeierstrassPreparation"}